  <title>GWeather.Location.new_world</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new_world(use_regions: Boolean): <link xref="GWeather.Location">GWeather.Location</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for gweather_location_new_world()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Creates a new <link xref="GWeather.Location"/> of type <link xref="GWeather.LocationLevel"/>.world,
representing a hierarchy containing all of the locations from
Locations.xml.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>use_regions</code></title>
  <p>whether or not to divide the world into regions</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="GWeather.LocationLevel"/>.world location, or
  <code>null</code> if Locations.xml could not be found or could not be parsed.</p>
</item>
